<1ST_LINE>u i BC-Japan-Crash     10-31 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Japan-Crash,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four US Marines Die in Helicopter Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American military helicopter crashed Monday
during a training mission on Okinawa, killing four U.S. Marines,
the United States Media Liaison Office said.
   Marine Master Sgt. Jake Rodrigues said two CH-46 Seaknight
helicopters were involved in routine training when one crashed in
remote, mountainous terrain on the Japanese island.
   The second helicopter returned to its base at Marine Corp Air
Station at Sutenma.
   Rodrigues declined to say how many people were on the helicopter
when it crashed or speculate as to why it went down, and said names
of the victims were being withheld pending notification of next of
kin.
   The two helicopters were assigned to Marine Medium Helicopter
Squadron 262.
   He said the accident was under investigation.
</TEXT>
