<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--JetFire     10-31 0111</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Jet Fire,0114</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cargo Jet Abandons Takeoff After Engine Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An El Al cargo jet with three
crewmembers aboard abandoned takeoff Monday after one of its
engines caught fire, apparently after being struck by a bird, an
airport spokesman said.
   None of the crew was injured in the accident at Amsterdam's
Schiphol Airport, said spokesman Rien Floris.
   Built-in fire extinguishing equipment put out the fire, although
one of the Boeing 747's wheels then caught fire because of the
pilot was forced to break sharply, Floris said.
   Airport firefighters soon extinguished that fire as well, he
said.
   The plane was flying to New York and Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
