<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Germany-Escape     10-31 0103</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Germany-Escape,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two East Germans Escape Into Bavaria</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two East German men climbed over
border barriers Monday to flee their communist homeland, police
reported.
   Border police in Bavaria state said the men told them their
escape was detected by East German troops but the soldiers did not
fire their weapons to try to stop them.
   The men, who were not identified, were uninjured, officials said.
   Police said 36 East Germans had fled into Bavaria this year.
   At least 351 East Germans have escaped to West Germany or West
Berlin in 1988, according to West German government statistics.
</TEXT>
