<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Britain-Soviets     10-31 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Soviets,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviets Arrive for Base Inspection</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENHAM COMMON, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A team of 10 Soviet military
experts came to Greenham Common air base Monday to hold inspections
under terms of the U.S.-Soviet treaty to eliminate
intermediate-range nuclear weapons.
   It is their second visit in less than four months. The Soviets
are permitted to inspect the U.S. cruise missile bases at Greenham
Common, 50 miles west of London, and Molesworth, 50 miles north of
the capital.
   The Soviets will disclose Tuesday which site they intend to
inspect.
   In July, they visited both sites.
   The Soviets will be allowed 20 inspection visits a year in the
West, with no more than half in any one country.
</TEXT>
