<HEAD>London Shares Fall</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices finished lower Monday after a
featureless session on the London Stock Exchange.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 6
points, or 0.3 percent, to 1,852.4.
   Volume was light, as 348.5 million shares changed hands,
compared with 484.2 million shares Friday.
   ``The market is rather finely balanced at this point, so without
a fresh set of economic justifications, we're liable to stay put,''
one dealer said.
   Dealers also noted a jittery atmosphere amid expectations that
Chancellor of the Exchequer Nigel Lawson would make a pivotal
economic speech on Tuesday.
   A partial recovery on Wall Street, where the Dow Jones
industrial average recovered more than 13 points after sinking 15
points, helped London equities off their intraday lows, dealers
said. By the close of the London day, the Dow Jones industrial
average was off 2.49 points at 2,147.40.
   The Financial Times 30-share index fell 7.2 points to 1,501.7.
The Financial Times 500 share index fell 2.26 to 1,054.73.
</TEXT>
