<HEAD>Beazer To Sell Three Units</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British businessman Brian C. Beazer disclosed
Monday preliminary agreements to sell three units of Koppers Co.
for a total of approximately $60 million.
   Beazer, looking to pay down debt from his $1.8 billion takeover
of Koppers, said the units are Koppers International Canada Ltd.,
which makes steel culvert pipe; Ivy Steel and Wire Co., a maker of
welded wire products, and Meadow Steel Products, which makes steel
reinforced construction material.
   The identity of the buyers was withheld.
   The three units were part of the construction and construction
materials division.
   Beazer said last week he intends to break up the company's
chemicals business and sell the various parts. A management group
earlier this year offered $660 million for the business, but the
deal fell through. Beazer said he expects to receive more than $660
million by selling the business in segments.
</TEXT>
